<font color="#FF0000">CASKET ATTACK</font><br>
<tt>Tue Feb 17 19:08:14 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
Here's a compelling incident that I want to verify.  A vet escorted his brother-in-law's body home in '68(KIA in VN).  At the San Franciso airport, he says four protesters people got onto the tarmac and attacked the casket.  The brother-in-law reported this and the Army investigated and came to the conclusion that this incident never happened.  They basically made a liar out of this person.  I believe the brother-in-law, but can find nothing to substantiate the incident. (DOD, FBI, Army, all say no files exist.) Is there anyone out there who has witnessed or heard of any such incidents--casket attacks on returning KIAs? Any pictures printed anywhere in news magazines of casket attacks at airports, cemeteries, etc.?  Anything will help.
